A World War II vet would like to pay his taxes but the IRS insists he'd dead.

Ohio man Siegfried Meinstein says that despite multiple attempts to convince the federal agency that he is, in fact, among the living, he has been unable to get someone to believe him.

The 94-year-old lives in an assisted living facility not far from Columbus. 

