'We are unable to process your tax return. Our records indicate that the person identified as the primary taxpayer…was deceased prior the tax year show on the tax form,' the IRS noted on a letter responding to Meinstein.

The IRS has told journalists that their people get information from the office of Social Security and that that was the best venue to reach an understanding. 

They've also sent Meinstein a letter curious as to why he prepaid $14,000 in taxes in 2014, and telling him that they'd lost his latest tax return.  

